&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager – EMEA (Scientific Instrumentation)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Netherlands (Eindhoven) or Remote within EMEA&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; Associate Director, Sales – EMEA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position combines technical expertise with commercial strategy to drive sales of advanced scientific instrumentation across academic, research, and industrial sectors in EMEA. It is ideal for a motivated professional with a strong scientific foundation and proven ability to build relationships, manage complex opportunities, and deliver impactful solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute sales plans targeting universities, research institutes, government agencies, and selected industrial customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage key accounts and identify new business opportunities across EMEA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with channel partners and internal teams to support customer engagement and technical sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to RFQs, RFIs, and public tenders with support from technical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company at scientific conferences and trade shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market trends and provide feedback to product teams on emerging research needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain CRM records and contribute to accurate forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Environmental Science, Chemistry, Physics, Geoscience, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in technical sales of analytical or scientific instruments,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills, with the ability to build trust across diverse stakeholder groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluency in English is required&lt;/strong&gt;;&amp;nbsp; German (working proficiency) and additional languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness and ability to travel across EMEA for key customer engagements and occasionally to the corporate HQ in Santa Clara, California.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultative Selling:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to uncover customer needs and propose tailored solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Skilled in building and maintaining long-term partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Thinking:&lt;/strong&gt; Capable of aligning sales activities with broader business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Curiosity:&lt;/strong&gt; Eagerness to learn and communicate complex scientific concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resilience &amp;amp; Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; Comfortable navigating diverse markets and evolving priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Versatility, flexibility, and a willingness to work within constantly changing priorities with enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;In possession of a valid passport, willing and allowed to travel to Picarro HQ in the USA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Allowed to work in the Netherlands (EU citizenship).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Picarro:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro, Inc. is the world&#39;s leading producer of greenhouse gas and optical stable isotope instruments, which are used in a wide variety of scientific and industrial applications, including: atmospheric science, air quality, greenhouse gas measurements, gas leak detection, food safety, hydrology, ecology and more. The company&#39;s products are all designed and manufactured at Picarro&#39;s Santa Clara, Ca

