&lt;li&gt;Contributes to organization growth by studying economic trends and revenue opportunities; including the financial implications of acquisition and expansion opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishes finance operational strategies by analyzing operations; identifying opportunities for improvement, cost reduction, and systems enhancement evaluating productivity, quality, and customer-service improvement; designing systems; resolving problems; implementing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shows visible commitment to the organization&#39;s mission and values of sustainability, transparency and positive impact on low-income communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Financial Management &lt;/em&gt;&amp;amp; &lt;em&gt;Planning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops pragmatic financial budget plans for executing on corporate strategy by modeling capital, manpower &amp;amp; facilities requirements, P&amp;amp;L performance, asset and liability management, facilities &amp;amp; staff requirements and establishing functional objectives in line with organizational&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees full financial and cash-flow planning and ensures availability of funds as needed (efficient use of cash, investments, working capital and long term capital sources).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitors financial performance by developing forecasts; measuring results; analyzing variances; initiating corrective actions; and developing improvement plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishes and provides ongoing monitoring of portfolio risk and financial control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Capitalization&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops and executes the organizations capitalization strategies, including pursuit of new debt investments, use of loan sales to raise capital, structuring new investment vehicles, identifying and cultivating new investors and managing ongoing banking/investor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees staff /consultants responsible for developing and executing investment prospectus for&lt;/li&gt

&lt;h1&gt;Client Program Specialist&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Client Program Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Customer Success&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Santa Clara, CA or Remote (US)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Position Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is part of Picarro&#39;s Customer Success organization, supporting managed-service programs for gas distribution utilities using Advanced Mobile Leak Detection (AMLD) technology. Picarro helps utilities detect natural gas leaks, quantify emissions, and prioritize repairs through its network intelligence platform.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Client Program Specialist (CPS), you&#39;ll help keep customer programs running day to day. Picarro delivers these programs through a managed-service model, with fieldwork—including driving, leak investigations, and related activities performed by service providers on Picarro&#39;s behalf. You&#39;ll serve as Picarro&#39;s primary operational point of contact for those providers, coordinating schedules, deliverables, reporting, and issue resolution while monitoring program performance through data review and QA/QC. You&#39;ll also help develop service providers&#39; analysts so they can gradually take ownership of routine reporting and quality assurance activities as their capabilities grow.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is well-suited for an early-career analyst who enjoys solving operational problems, working with data, and coordinating across multiple stakeholders. It provides hands-on experience in project management, operations, customer success, and analytics, with a clear path toward broader program management responsibilities as you grow.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the service provider’s primary day-to-day point of contact at Picarro, coordinating schedules, deliverables, and issues across a portfolio of concurrent engagements, and ensuring service provider activities meet Picarro’s operating standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track program status, risks, and dependencies across active engagements; flag issues and escalate to the Client Program Manager with recommended next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run and maintain reports and dashboards, and perform QA/QC on operational data to ensure accuracy and completeness before customer delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze operational and performance data to identify trends and risks, and translate findings into clear updates for the Client Program Manager and customer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide first-line software support to internal and customer users of Picarro’s platforms, escalating complex issues to the appropriate team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with the service provider, customer contacts, and internal teams to keep programs on track, and partner with the Client Program Manager on customer-facing updates and reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate program documentation, manuals, and troubleshooting guides, and contribute to workflow and process improvements across engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, engineering, analytics, operations, or a related field, plus 2+ years of experience in data analysis, project coordination, or operations (internships, co-ops, or significant academic project work count).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, with the ability to work confidently in large, complex datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated attention to detail and clear documentation habits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office, with advanced Excel skills (e.g., pivot tables, formulas, data validation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills; comfortable engaging directly with externa

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Field Application Scientist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Scientist – EMEA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Eindhoven, Netherlands (Onsite with travel)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; Associate Director, Sales – EMEA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a skilled and motivated Application Scientist to join our team in Eindhoven. This role blends scientific expertise with customer engagement and technical support, contributing directly to Picarro’s growth across EMEA. You will be based at our Eindhoven office and lab, where you’ll manage day-to-day lab operations and support field activities. The position requires regular travel across Europe and to the United States, with no travel restrictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the daily operations of the Eindhoven lab, including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently leading application development projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting product demonstrations in the office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tailoring solutions to real-world applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring a safe, organised, and productive environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training customers and partners onsite in Eindhoven&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform product installations, training, and follow-up to ensure customer satisfaction and long-term engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Application Science team to develop scientific content (e.g., abstracts, presentations) for conferences and exhibitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Sales colleagues, Support teams, and Product Managers to identify new business opportunities and share customer feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Picarro at conferences, trade shows, and customer visits across the EMEA region. Travel requirements may vary—some months may involve up to 50% travel, while others significantly less, depending on business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a collaborative, inclusive team culture that values diverse perspectives, mutual respect, and continuous learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Geoscience, Earth Sciences, Environmental Science, Chemical Engineering, or a related field (Master’s or PhD welcome).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Several years of experience working with laser optical instruments, isotope ratio mass spectrometry, or trace gas analysers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills in English; additional languages (e.g., German, French) are a plus.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to explain complex technical concepts in a clear, engaging way to diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data analysis and visualisation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in cross-functional teams and contributing to a supportive, inclusive work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness and ability to travel freely across Europe and to the United States.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Field Deployment Engineer - Oil, Gas &amp;amp; Chemicals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel: ≤70%&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote USA, CA or TX preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro&#39;s Fenceline Monitoring Solution delivers continuous, real-time emissions intelligence to refineries and chemical plants. The technology works. The harder challenge — and the one that determines whether a pilot becomes a long-term program — is the early engagement: ensuring that Environmental, HSSE, and Operations teams understand the data in front of them, integrate it into how they work, and begin to operate differently because of it. That is the work of the Forward Deployed Engineer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FDE is embedded at customer sites during pilots and early-stage engagements. This role sets the benchmark for how Picarro unlocks value — changing the way operators and HSSE practitioners engage with real-time emissions data, moving from passive, retrospective review toward active, real-time decision-making. Success means customers take faster action on the signals that matter, reduce emissions, reduce risk, and build a more operationally excellent emissions management practice — with PicarroLink at the center of how they work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are energized by change — specifically, by the challenge of shifting how an industry operates. You are not here to maintain the status quo or run a passive playbook. You walk into a refinery control room or HSSE office, earn trust quickly, and get people working differently. That is what drives you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are comfortable with emissions management technology. You understand emissions monitoring — detection, attribution, LDAR, real-time data and can speak credibly with the people using it. You are practical and hands-on in nature, and you are comfortable navigating a refinery or chemicals facility – e.g., by driving a survey vehicle, running real-time analytics in the field. You are energized by leading on the software side: Demonstrating how real-time emissions data and analytics fits into daily workflows, coaching teams through the shift from scheduled reporting to real-time signal-driven decision-making and making digital a natural part of how Environmental and Operations teams work. You bring energy to that. You make it feel achievable, not foreign.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You collaborate naturally with Customer Success and Product teams, because you recognize that your customer-facing observations are among the highest-quality inputs those functions receive. You translate adoption gaps into actionable product feedback, and you work with Customer Success to ensure that what gets tracked and built reflects real-world operational needs. You hold yourself accountable to customer outcomes — not to task completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are also motivated by building something. The adoption models, training approaches, and workflow integration playbooks being developed right now will define how Picarro delivers at scale. The person in this role will shape them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If that sounds like the work you have been looking for, we want to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DUTIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Deployment Engineer – Oil, Gas &amp;amp; Chemicals is responsible for driving adoption, enablement, and value realization at customer sites during pilots and early-stage engagements. Working with one customer at a time, the FDE ensures that Picarro&#39;s Fenceline Monitoring Solution and PicarroLink platform are embedded into Environmental, HSSE, and Operations workflows as an active, real-time tool — not a passive data archive. Delivery, commissioning, and hardware support are handled by Picarro&#39;s Operations and Delivery function; the FDE collaborates with that team but is focused entirely on the adoption and enablement work that determines w

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Manager, Natural Gas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Santa Clara, CA - Onsite&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro is looking for a talented and driven Product Manager to join our Natural Gas team at our Santa Clara headquarters. This is an exciting opportunity for an early-to-mid career professional with a strong technical foundation to take meaningful ownership across the full product lifecycle — from concept and requirements through development, launch, and iteration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work at the intersection of hardware and software, partnering closely with R&amp;amp;D, engineering, data analytics, sales, field operations, and customer program management teams to define and deliver products that reinforce Picarro&#39;s position as the industry leader in data-driven methane emissions management and network intelligence for the Natural Gas market. Reporting to the Sr. Director of Product Strategy, you will help shape the roadmap for Picarro&#39;s gas product portfolio and grow into a key voice within the product organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own your product roadmap. &lt;/strong&gt;Define, prioritize, and communicate a product roadmap for natural gas solutions that balances near-term customer needs with long-term strategic bets, across both hardware and software dimensions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive market and customer insight. &lt;/strong&gt;Conduct customer interviews, analyze field and usage data, and synthesize market research to identify high-impact opportunities, validate product concepts, and maintain a deep understanding of the natural gas and energy landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Write clear requirements. &lt;/strong&gt;Author Marketing Requirements Documents (MRDs), Product Requirements Documents (PRDs), user stories, and acceptance criteria for both hardware features and software releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead cross-functional execution. &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with R&amp;amp;D, engineering, manufacturing, QA, software development, and data analytics teams to bring products to market on time and within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Champion Agile delivery. &lt;/strong&gt;Serve as an active product owner in Agile scrum cycles — participate in sprint planning, backlog grooming, story review, and retrospectives for software and data platform initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support hardware NPI. &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate with engineering and operations on New Product Introduction (NPI) and Product Lifecycle (PLC) processes, ensuring smooth transitions from development to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable the commercial team. &lt;/strong&gt;Develop sales collateral, training materials, and competitive positioning to support the gas business team; respond to technical customer inquiries and assist in pre-sales activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Represent Picarro externally. &lt;/strong&gt;Present products and solutions at industry conferences, trade shows, and customer sites; build lasting relationships with key gas utility accounts and industry stakeholders to collaborate on new product breakthroughs and establish reference standards for the industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measure success. &lt;/strong&gt;Define KPIs for product initiatives; track adoption and field performance post-launch and drive continuous improvement based on data and customer feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay ahead of the market. &lt;/strong&gt;Monitor the competitive landscape, emerging technologies, and regulatory trends in methane emissions detection, leak detection, and natural gas network management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Head of Product – Technology/Analyzer Platform&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Santa Clara, CA or Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Chief Product/Strategy Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Product Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro&#39;s analyzer is the one piece of technology every product line depends on — Fenceline, Workplace Monitoring, CEMS, AMLD, Natural Gas, and Analytical Instruments all run on the same CRDS core. As Picarro scales its Compliance-as-a-Service model across more verticals, that core needs a single accountable owner: someone who sets one roadmap, defends it against one-off forks, and turns next-generation programs like Loki and compact-cavity CRDS into shipped platform improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Head of Product to own that roadmap end-to-end. You&#39;ll sit at the intersection of optics, firmware, and the commercial needs of every Systems and Solution PM building on top of the platform — turning competing requests into a prioritized roadmap that makes the whole portfolio better, not just one product. This is a build role: define what “platform” means at Picarro, then prove it by shipping the modernization work already underway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A subject matter expertise in optics is not required. Still, a strong technical background and experience with hardware or instrumentation platforms are essential. This role earns credibility with engineering first, then translates that into a roadmap the rest of the business can build on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own &lt;/strong&gt;the single technology/analyzer platform roadmap (CRDS and BB-CRDS engine, firmware, common APIs) that underpins every Picarro product line, from Fenceline and Workplace Monitoring to CEMS, AMLD, Natural Gas, and Analytical Instruments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translate &lt;/strong&gt;roadmap requests from Systems and Solution PMs into prioritized platform investments, and hold the line against forks that fragment the core.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive &lt;/strong&gt;major platform programs (Loki/next-gen analyzer modernization, compact-cavity CRDS, optical feedback) with clear specs, milestones, and exit criteria from concept through commercial release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner &lt;/strong&gt;with Engineering leadership on architecture decisions governing modularity, serviceability, and manufacturability across the analyzer family.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set &lt;/strong&gt;and defend platform performance, cost, and reliability targets, balancing what&#39;s technically possible against what verticals need to win deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Represent &lt;/strong&gt;the platform roadmap in the Quarterly Portfolio Review and other cross-functional planning forums, translating technical trade-offs for sales and executive audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work &lt;/strong&gt;directly with R&amp;amp;D, manufacturing, and select strategic customers to validate platform direction before it&#39;s locked into the roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some travel to manufacturing, R&amp;amp;D, and customer sites is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a technical field (engineering, physics, chemistry, or related) is required; MS or PhD is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years in product management or engineering leadership for hardware or instrumentation platforms, ideally with optical, spectroscopy, or analytical instrumentation experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of owning a shared technology platform across multiple

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: Regulatory Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Location: Remote &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Term: Full-time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel: &amp;lt; 10%&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro, Inc. has an opportunity for a CEMS Regulatory Manager to assist the Industrial Solutions team with regulatory reporting for continuous emissions monitoring systems (CEMS) and daily quality assurance reviews. This position is remote but will require occasional travel to our headquarters in Santa Clara, CA, and to some client sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primary duties of this position include, but are not limited to: quarterly emissions report generation, Relative Accuracy Test Audit (RATA) review, and proficiency in the Compliance and Emissions Data Reporting Interface (CEDRI) and the Electronic Reporting Tool (ERT). The successful candidate will work closely with the Field Operations team to build proficiency in this area and develop SOPs for regulatory compliance. Other duties may include assisting with new-method development, preparing conference presentations, and generating fenceline monitoring system reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be personable, have a strong background in regulatory compliance, and hold exceptional organizational skills. This position is expected to grow, and the successful candidate will be well-positioned to manage a team of regulatory specialists in the future.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile CEMS emissions reports in compliance with federal, state, and/or local regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review RATA test plans and reports to ensure they are conducted properly. Upon completion of RATA review, it may be necessary to input the report into the ERT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track CEMS downtime and communicate with project managers and the Program Manager about any compliance concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop SOPs for report generation and use of CEDRI/ERT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep a thorough and well-organized database of all reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop site-specific monitoring plans, monitoring plans, and quality assurance plans for CEMS, workplace, and fenceline monitoring systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up-to-date on new regulations to assist the business development team with future strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop presentations for internal use, for clients, and for tradeshows where needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train new employees on the position and ensure their growth and development, while maintaining a strict schedule for regulatory compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold bi-weekly calls with relevant Project Managers and Directors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in new method development for future monitoring solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approximately 6+ years of experience in the emissions monitoring space or equal time working in an industrial setting in an EHS position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with RATA review, quarterly/semiannual CEMS reporting, and the ERT, or the ability to learn these skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in MS Office, specifically Excel and Outlook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience navigating a Data Acquisition System (DAS) or the ability to learn this skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel approximately 10% of the time, including to our headquarters in Santa Clara, CA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent education plus job experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in the emissions monitoring space or equal time working in an industrial

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Manager – Industrial Solutions – Sterilizers Americas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; US – Flexible, with ~75% Travel (Explore, Connect, Deliver!)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Term:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time – Drive growth and make an impact!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to drive growth and deliver impactful solutions in environmental compliance? As a &lt;strong&gt;Sales Manager for Industrial Solutions – Sterilizers Americas&lt;/strong&gt;, you will operate as a high-performing individual contributor, owning your territory and revenue goals while collaborating closely with a cross-functional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll combine technical expertise with commercial execution to expand the adoption of advanced emissions monitoring solutions that help customers meet EPA standards and navigate Clean Air Act requirements. This role is especially focused on the growing Ethylene Oxide sterilization market across medical, spice, packaging, transport, and warehousing sectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll act as a trusted advisor to customers - leading complex, consultative sales cycles - while partnering internally with business development, product, and field teams to deliver tailored, high-impact solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Impact &amp;amp; Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a self-driven sales professional who thrives on ownership and accountability but understands that winning requires strong teamwork. You’ll take the lead on opportunities from prospecting through close, while leveraging internal expertise to strengthen your approach and outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your success will come from balancing &lt;strong&gt;independent execution&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;strong&gt;collaborative problem-solving&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring customers receive both technical depth and commercial value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute territory sales strategy, driving revenue growth within the sterilizer and industrial solutions market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full sales cycle from lead generation and technical discovery to proposal development, negotiation, and closing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and grow key accounts while identifying new opportunities and expanding your network across the Americas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead consultative, solution-based sales engagements, translating complex technical offerings into clear customer value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with business development, product and field teams, to deliver tailored solutions and proposals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create compelling proposals and system quotes, aligning customer requirements with the PICARRO solution portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate CRM records and forecasts, ensuring strong pipeline visibility and planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage customers across multiple channels (in-person, virtual, phone) and travel extensively to build relationships and close deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet and exceed sales targets, demonstrating consistent performance and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share market insights and customer feedback to support product development and strategic direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company at industry events, trade shows, and conferences to generate leads and strengthen brand presence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in engineering, environmental science, chemistry, business, or related field (or equivalent experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5+ years of experience in technical industrial sales&lt;/strong&gt;, preferably in environmental monitoring, analytical instrumentation, or regulated industries.&lt;/li&gt;
