&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior NPI Engineer – Optomechanical Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Santa Clara, CA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced, hands-on NPI Engineer to lead the transition of next-generation spectroscopy products from prototype through pilot build and into volume manufacturing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picarro’s products deliver real-time measurements of critical gases at parts-per-billion and parts-per-trillion levels. In this role, you will take ownership of translating advanced CRDS-based optomechanical designs into robust, scalable, and high-yield manufacturing processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will operate at the critical interface between R&amp;amp;D and manufacturing—driving productization strategy, leading build execution, and ensuring that complex optical systems can be manufactured with precision, repeatability, and cost-effectiveness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the Director of Spectrometer Engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a seasoned productization / NPI engineer who thrives in ambiguity and takes full ownership of getting products into production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads by example as a &lt;strong&gt;hands-on builder and problem solver&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owns complex builds and &lt;strong&gt;drives issues to closure across disciplines&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influences design decisions to ensure manufacturability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creates processes, tooling, and documentation from first principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acts as a &lt;strong&gt;technical bridge between engineering, manufacturing, and suppliers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is comfortable leading builds, mentoring junior engineers and technicians, and making technical trade-offs that balance performance, manufacturability, and cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPI Leadership &amp;amp; Product Transfer Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead NPI from prototype through pilot build and production ramp&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own engineering builds from prototype to early production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment across R&amp;amp;D, operations, quality, and supply chain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure successful transfer to manufacturing with clear ownership of yield, quality, and readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design for Manufacturability &amp;amp; Productization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead DFM/DFA/DFX to optimize manufacturability, reliability, and cost&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence design through tolerance, alignment, and process constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify high-risk areas early and drive design and process changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Development &amp;amp; Industrialization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and validate assembly processes for precision optomechanical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define process flows, controls, and acceptance criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish repeatable alignment processes and production windows&lt;/li&gt;
